(44, 17, 8, 43, 11, 48, 48, 'troubled the people and the rulers', 'Fear of Public Reaction', 'Both passages emphasize the troubling effect of Jesus'' influence on the people and rulers. In Acts, the disturbance among the city rulers parallels the concern in John about losing their place and nation due to Jesus'' growing following.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
