(44, 17, 16, 19, 119, 158, 158, NULL, 'Grief Over Idolatry and Transgression', 'This connection highlights the emotional response to idolatry and disobedience. Both passages emphasize a sense of grief over the people''s failure to adhere to God''s word.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 17, 16, 2, 32, 19, 20, 'wholly given to idolatry', 'Idolatry and Anger', 'This connection highlights the theme of idolatry provoking strong emotional responses. Both Paul and Moses react to the pervasive idolatry in their contexts, with Paul’s spirit stirred and Moses’ anger waxed hot.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
